# =============================================================================
# .cruxeignore
# =============================================================================
#
# This file tells Cruxe which files and directories to skip during
# indexing. Place a copy named `.cruxeignore` in your project root
# and uncomment or add patterns as needed.
#
# Syntax is identical to .gitignore:
#   - Blank lines are ignored.
#   - Lines starting with # are comments.
#   - Standard glob patterns work (*, ?, [abc]).
#   - A leading / anchors the pattern to the project root.
#   - A trailing / matches directories only.
#   - A leading ! negates the pattern (re-includes a previously excluded path).
#
# Patterns are evaluated top-to-bottom; later rules override earlier ones.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build outputs
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
target/
dist/
build/
out/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Dependencies
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
vendor/
.venv/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Generated code
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.generated.*
*.pb.go
*_generated.rs

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Binary files
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.exe
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
*.wasm
*.pyc
*.class

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Minified files
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.min.js
*.min.css

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IDE / editor files
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS files
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Lock files
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
Cargo.lock

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Negation patterns
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Use the ! prefix to re-include a file that was excluded by an earlier rule.
# Negation patterns are evaluated in order, so they must appear AFTER the rule
# they override.
#
# Examples:
#
#   # Exclude all of vendor/, but keep a specific vendored library:
#   vendor/
#   !vendor/critical-lib/
#
#   # Exclude all generated code, but index a specific protobuf file:
#   *.pb.go
#   !api/v1/service.pb.go
#
#   # Exclude all lock files, but keep Cargo.lock (recommended for binaries):
#   Cargo.lock
#   !Cargo.lock
